Load labels labels = {} with open("input/essential_data/rec_labels_test_hidden.txt") as f: next(f) for line in f: parts = line.strip().split(",") rec_id = int(parts[0]) labels[rec_id] = [int(x) for x in parts[1:] if x.isdigit()] # Prepare features def load_features(): seg = pd.read_csv( "input/supplemental_data/segment_features.txt", header=None, skiprows=1, names=["rec_id", "seg_id"] + [f"sf_{i}" for i in range(38)], ) seg_agg = seg.groupby("rec_id").agg(["mean", "std", "min", "max"]).fillna(0) seg_agg.columns = [f"{i}_{j}" for i, j in seg_agg.columns] hist = pd.read_csv( "input/supplemental_data/histogram_of_segments.txt", header=None, skiprows=1, names=["rec_id"] + [f"hist_{i}" for i in range(100)], ) return hist.merge(seg_agg, on="rec_id", how="left").fillna(0) features = load_features().set_index("rec_id") mlb = MultiLabelBinarizer(classes=range(19)) y = pd.DataFrame(mlb.fit_transform(labels.values()), index=labels.keys()) # Prepare data X_train = features.loc[train_ids] X_test = features.loc[test_ids] scaler = StandardScaler() X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train) test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test) # Train per-species models test_probs = np.zeros((len(test_ids), 19)) val_aucs = [] for species in range(19): print(f"\nTraining species {species}") y_species = y[species].loc[train_ids] if y_species.sum() == 0: print(f"Skipping species {species} (no positives)") test_probs[:, species] = 0 val_aucs.append(np.nan) continue model = LGBMClassifier( n_estimators=2000, learning_rate=0.05, num_leaves=127, subsample=0.8, colsample_bytree=0.8, random_state=42, n_jobs=-1, verbose=-1, # Move verbose here ) model.fit(X_scaled, y_species) # Validation prediction val_preds = model.predict_proba(X_scaled)[:, 1] species_auc = roc_auc_score(y_species, val_preds) val_aucs.append(species_auc) # Test prediction test_probs[:, species] = model.predict_proba(test_scaled)[:, 1] print(f"Species {species} AUC: {species_auc:.4f}") # Calculate overall validation AUC mean_auc = np.nanmean(val_aucs) print(f"\nOverall Validation AUC: {mean_auc:.4f}") # Create submission submission = [] for i, rec_id in enumerate(test_ids): for species in range(19): submission.append( {"Id": rec_id * 100 + species, "Probability": test_probs[i, species]} ) sub_df = pd.DataFrame(submission) sub_df.to_csv("submission/submission.csv", index=False) print(f"Submission saved with {len(sub_df)} rows")
